article.headline: Florida A&M 77, Howard 74
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Tony Tate scored 26 points and Jonathan Kelly hit a go-ahead shot with 17 seconds left Monday to lead Florida A&M to a 77-74 win over Howard. Kelly made a short jumper to give Florida A&M a 75-74 lead, and the Rattlers' James Pattman followed with two free throws with two seconds left. Howard's Darek Mitchell tried a 3-point shot as time expired, but the ball rimmed out and bounced away. Howard has lost seven consecutive games and eight of its last nine. Darius Glover added 20 points for Florida A&M (6-11, 5-5 MEAC) and Kelly finished with 10. Cliffone Ault led Howard (5-13, 2-7 MEAC) with 20 points. Will Gant scored 14 and Jason Trotter had 10. Howard led 41-35 at halftime after building leads of as many as 13 points. But Tate scored seven points to spark a 9-2 run early in the second half to give Florida A&M a 51-48 lead. The lead changed hands seven times the rest of the way. Florida A&M opened the game with an 8-3 lead. But Howard, after inserting five reserves, scored the next 10 points and never trailed again in the first half.
